This track shows guide RNA sequences, including PAM sites (NGG),
for coding sequences. Feature info also includes T7 or SP6
promoter based oligo sequences for expressing the sgRNA in a
plasmid. The distinct primers are TAATACGACTCACTATA
for T7 and ATTTAGGTGACACTATA for SP6.

metadata.Info:
The putative transcription factor binding sites are identified by running fimo on X. laevis 9.2 genome
using motifs downloaded from CIS-BP database, and filtered by the peaks of epigenetic data,
including H3K4me1, H3K4me3, P300 at stage 10.5.

metadata.Info:
This pseudogene track includes both processed pseudogenes (colored green)
and NCBI pseudogenes (colored yellow). The processed pseudogenes are
generated by aligning protein sequences to genome sequences,
merging adjacent homologies, and realigning protein sequences
to genome sequences using fasta. The method was presented
in two papers by Zhang et al (2002 and 2003).
